                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to <persName
                            type="to">Baron de Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 26, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In absence of Governor Foster, the private secretary to the governor telegraphs
                    me that the next regular term of the grand jury in Madison Parish is in January,
                    but that it is the intention of the parish authorities to call a special term
                    before then, of the date of which information is promised as soon as the judge
                    can be reached.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
